3. Plugin and Extension Monetization Addendum
In addition to the rights granted under the MIT License, the following terms apply specifically to plugins, tools, or commercial extensions for NOWA-Engine:

3.1 Plugin Development and Distribution
You may create plugins, tools, or extensions for NOWA-Engine.
Plugins must adhere to the official API guidelines provided by NOWA-Engine.

3.2 Plugin Commercialization
You may monetize your plugins and tools.
Paid plugins/tools must be sold or distributed via the official NOWA-Engine Marketplace unless explicitly permitted by Lukas Kalinowski.
A revenue-sharing model may apply for plugins sold via the official Marketplace.
Third-party plugin sellers are required to share sales data and revenue reports with Lukas Kalinowski when requested.

3.3 License Compliance
Plugins may not circumvent licensing or DRM mechanisms of NOWA-Engine.
Plugins that modify or interfere with core engine functionality in unauthorized ways may be considered a violation of this license.

3.4 Branding and Trademarks
Plugins may not use the NOWA-Engine logo, branding, or trademarks without prior written consent from Lukas Kalinowski.
Approved usage must follow branding guidelines provided by Lukas Kalinowski.

4. Commercial Use of NOWA-Engine (NOWA Pro License)
While the core engine is free under the MIT License, the following terms apply to commercial projects:

4.1 Commercial License Requirement
If you use NOWA-Engine in a closed-source, commercial product, you must obtain a NOWA-Engine Pro License.
Licensing fees or revenue-sharing terms will be defined in a separate commercial license agreement.

4.2 Commercial Licensing Contact
For obtaining a Pro License, contact us at:
* lukas.kalinowski1505@gmail.com
* http://www.lukas-kalinowski.com/Homepage/?page_id=23

